                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I use the compact slider timer from <a href="http://www.horizonsoutpost.com/eq/timer.asp" target="_blank" class="postlink">here</a>...but only sometimes.  Here's a pic:
<br />
<a href="http://www.horizonsoutpost.com/eq/timer.asp" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.horizonsoutpost.com/eq/images/timers_compact_faded.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />

<br />
The only timer I have ever seen that "clocks every spell" was part of ShowEQ, which violates the EULA.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="icon_twisted.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
You should be sure you want a timer before you use the one linked above.  You need to: know your spell durations, pick a window in EQ that you don't use for the timer to replace, create the custom timer, install it to your current UI, remember to bring it up before the spell you want to time is cast, and set the slider manually to mark the start time for each spell.
<br />

<br />
It's a bit of a hassle, but when you are really trying to eke the most efficiency out of your mana, it can be worth it.  I think it would be nice if EQ provided an optional "spell x is about to expire in 5 seconds" or even graphical timers for each spell you cast or receive.
<br />

<br />
When all is said and done, it's a matter of taste, really.  Some folks even use egg timers and the like on their computer desk.  Best of luck finding something that works well for you. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Haewud &lt;Heroes&gt;
<br />
"A person who believes, as she did, that things fit: that there is a whole of which one is a part, and that in being a part one is whole: such a person has no desire whatever, at any time, to play God.  Only those who have denied their being yearn to play at it." -Ursula  K. LeGuin, <span style="font-style: italic">The Lathe of Heaven</span>
<br />
<a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewtopic.php?p=18979" target="_blank" class="postlink">E65.243/L h- 2.8khp ft15 G+++&lt;3 e+++@ o- T+ L(+++)+ H++(+++)@ f++ g b- c+++@ t++++ !D X@</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
