                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually, Haewud, I've experienced no performance hit to the game at all, even when running on my PIII 650 server (admittedly running old models on that one though).  My main machine is an AMD Athalon XP 2000, with 1GB of PC2100 RAM.  Not a monster, but nothing to sneeze at either.
<br />

<br />
On either machine, really the only performance issue I've experienced is that in a really laggy zone the speech would get a little choppy, and that's a problem with the tool, not EQ.  I <span style="font-style: italic">am</span> running on Windows 2000, and I've only run more recent versions, so it's possible they've made performance improvements.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=304783" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fallere T`Vala</a>
