                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I use the aformentinoed parser, it covers 3 basic areas
<br />

<br />
Debuffs:Mez(it differentiates between which mez you're using to give ya the right time, currently not set up to work with mez mastery, but that's not a prob, would take 30 sec of changes)  Slows, cripple, and dots, tash, and even charm(will just time to the 7:30 duration, but with a decent cha and TD 3, most of your charms will go to duration anyway, so over 1/2 you breaks planned is a godsend)  Will give 90, 30, and 10 sec warnings before imminent 7:30 pet break.  I cant tell you how many ppl will only charm with me after seeing timed breaks.
<br />

<br />
Buffs:just about everything you cast(voq, tranq, kei, god, haste, ndt, see invis, imp invis etc)
<br />
Most common raidbuffs(virtue, pot9, symbol, sd, bss, focus, sta, agi) and specifcally dru buffs(soe, sow, and seasons are the 3 i can think of off the top of my head)  It can also take the extended enhancement of your fav dru and apply it to buffs htey cast
<br />

<br />
General awarenss:Notifies you of interrupts, fizzles, spell recovery not yet met, others slows, tashes and cripples(when both you and the target are close enuf you get the msg put into your log, tad buggy), your DPS, or the DPS of your pet, kills per hour, when an NPC is gating, the # of targets hit with your last MGB, nice jingling coin sound when something on your trader sells, when anyone says moving or add, anything said in group, guild, or a chat channel(very small chirp on the last 3)  and will also read your tells outloud to you.  
<br />

<br />
Sorta 4th area here, but i didnt include it above because it's not workin so hot for me atm
<br />
Add'ly, tho i have been having probs with this, you can track a raid in your story window, and have it outputted(2 diff version of this, one does sql output, other is html i think)  will track who came, when, and when they left.  Who looted what @ what time.  And of course, the chanter's favorite:list of mez breakers, and # of breaks per person.  
<br />

<br />
For everything it does, if you dont like it, you can comment out a line, and it wont do it.  If you think of anything else that hits your log file, or your /note file, you can have this trigger stuff for you too.  (for example, at one point if i said /note droga 1 it would set up a timer for 19:30 and say "30 seconds to 1" when it expired, thus allowing me to time droga pops as long as i remebered which spot mob # 1 spanwed in.)
<br />

<br />

<br />
If you're worried about preformance issues, your best bet's to run it on a 2nd machine and have your logfile shared over the network, you need to fool eqwa into thinking you've got EQ running, but that's as simple as naming any other program eqgame.exe and running it.(i used to run EQ on a celeron 400 with 768 meg of PC 133 ram and a 1/2 burnt geforce 2, i had a pentium 133 running my parser, keep in mind, this was under 6 months ago)
<br />

<br />
Fyi for multi-boxers, it doesnt run well with 2x copies on 1 machine, they have a shared memeory space i think, any addons for 1 copy of EQ will be applied to the other as well.  Because of this you either have to run a parser on each machine, or just cope with it(i chose just cope with it so i can just use 1 set of headphones, works well enuf still)
<br />

<br />
May i also reccommend speeding up the speach agent a bit, the default can get a bit congested if you're in a hellstorm of adds, and any tells will only make it worse. simply speeding up the rate it talks tho all but removes this problem.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
